nd experience their migration trajectories.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAsianszForeign countries. 0aEmigration and immigrationxSocial aspects. 0aHuman bodyxSocial aspects. 4aAsian Studies. 4aContemporary Society. 4aPsychology. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aMigration, Body, Ethnicity, Gender, Sexuality.1 aBaas, Michiel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaas, Michiel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaey, Grace, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGamburd, Michele Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKhan, Hareem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLam, Theodora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Alex Yang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahdavi, Pardis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOng, Michelle G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPande, Amrita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlatt, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpitzer, Denise L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYang, Peidong, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYen, Khoo Choon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYeoh, Brenda S. A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection 